procedures.name: Blood Draw
procedures.label: Venipuncture
procedures.description: Collection of venous blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), clinical safety laboratory assessments (serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation), infectious disease screening, and pregnancy testing.

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.name: Urine Collection
procedures.label: Urine Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of urine for urinalysis, drug screening, pregnancy testing, and 24-hour measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Fecal Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of individual fecal samples for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: Complete or symptom-driven physical examination including assessments of the cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Measurement of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram
procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Recording of the heart's electrical activity using a 12-lead ECG, performed in triplicate at specified timepoints.

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.name: Oral Administration of Investigational Product
procedures.label: Drug Administration
procedures.description: Oral administration of ALXN1840 tablets (15 mg or 30 mg) once daily.

procedures.name: Anthropometric Measurements
procedures.label: Height, Weight, BMI
procedures.description: Measurement of height, weight, and calculation of Body Mass Index (BMI).

procedures.name: Medical History Collection
procedures.label: Medical History
procedures.description: Collection of participant medical history, demographics, Wilson Disease (WD) history, and prior WD treatment.

code.decode: Urinalysis, by dip stick or tablet reagent for bilirubin, glucose, hemoglobin, ketones, leukocytes, nitrite, pH, protein, specific gravity, urobilinogen, any number of these constituents; automated, with microscopy

procedures.name: Screening for Infectious Diseases
procedures.label: HIV, Hepatitis Screen
procedures.description: Blood screening for HIV, hepatitis B, and hepatitis C.

procedures.name: Cannula Placement
procedures.label: IV Cannulation
procedures.description: Insertion of an intravenous cannula to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

procedures.name: Dietary Sample Collection
procedures.label: Food/Fluid Sampling
procedures.description: Collection of samples from all meal and fluid batches for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Bowel and Urine Monitoring
procedures.label: Intake/Output Monitoring
procedures.description: Monitoring and recording of urination and bowel movements.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure Monitor
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Device
medicalDevices.description: Completely automated device for assessing blood pressure and heart rate measurements.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead ECG Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms.

medicalDevices.name: Intravenous Cannula
medicalDevices.label: IV Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A cannula placed in a vein to allow for repeated blood sampling while minimizing needle sticks.

medicalDevices.name: Inductively Coupled Plasma Mass Spectrometry Analyzer
medicalDevices.label: ICP-MS
medicalDevices.description: Laboratory equipment used to determine the copper and molybdenum concentration of food, fluid, urine, and fecal samples.
